Person-in-the-Middle Proxy Lab
Client-Side Bypass Using Burp Suite
ğŸ“Œ Overview

This lab focused on understanding Person-in-the-Middle (PITM) proxy techniques using Burp Suite to intercept and manipulate web traffic.
The objective was to bypass client-side security controls in a vulnerable web application by modifying HTTP requests before they reached the server.

The lab simulated a real-world scenario where a user with $0.00 account balance attempts to purchase expensive items by exploiting client-side trust flaws.

ğŸ¯ Lab Objectives

Understand how web traffic flows between a browser and a server

Configure and use Burp Suite as an intercepting proxy

Intercept HTTP requests and modify parameters

Bypass client-side validation logic

Demonstrate why server-side validation is critical

